# DEEP-DIVE DOSSIER RUBRIC

This rubric is for the deep-dive pass — the second research layer that converts a "{gate_values_primary}" first-pass card into an article-ready dossier.

## Goal
Produce a full dossier using `topic-dossier-template.md` that is meaningfully richer than the first-pass card: more sources, more texture, more specificity, and concrete post angles.

## Minimum acceptance bar
A deep-dive dossier is acceptable only if it includes:
- 6-10 sources total, at least 2 primary or contemporaneous
- All template sections filled (no blank sections)
- At least 2 strong pull quotes or memorable phrasing examples
- At least 1 named person, company, or institution with specific detail beyond what the first-pass card covered
- Drama / tension / absurdity section has concrete incidents, not just vibes
- At least 2 distinct future post angles with enough detail to start drafting from
- Material that goes beyond the first-pass card — new facts, new sources, new angles
{deepdive_acceptance_extra}

## What "goes beyond" means
- New sources not already cited in the first-pass card
- Specific incidents, dates, names, dollar amounts, or data the card didn't have
- Pull quotes from people involved, not retrospective summaries
- At least one detail specific enough to surprise a knowledgeable reader
{deepdive_beyond_extra}

